    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "14fbc9a3dcccdad1",
      "text": "The selection and the matching process that lead to the formation of roles and responsibilities can have a significant influence on the level of trust team members feel for each other. [[Trust]] has been established as the basis for constructive team work (Lencioni 2002)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "1e38dfc97117f102",
      "text": "Finally, the formation phase of a team often falls together with the starting phase of a project – a team gets formed to pursue a project –, and thus the content the team will work on also gets defined in the same phase. Even if this happens on an abstract vision level in the beginning, it will often set the direction and the tone of further work."
